Retry handles failures you hope go away (exception-driven, jittered backoff to spare a struggling server); polling handles success that hasn't completed yet (field-driven, fixed interval on a healthy server). So I'd just wrap the DescribeTaskStatus call with @retry for transient blips and leave the poll loop alone.


```python
@retry
def _describe_task_status(self, req):
  return self.client.DescribeTaskStatus(req)    

...

while retries < max_retries:                                                                                                                                                                                               
  resp = self._describe_task_status(req)   # survives transient 5xx/429/DNS blips 

```
